replies.bodyText:
I find the existing formulation actually a bit confusing: since multiple Fs are accepted this thew me off a bit initially: It represents the most significant digit of the seconds fraction and all trailing 0s will be printed to meet the number ofF s in the pattern:

just the first F corresponds to the most significant digit;
there are multiple fractions a second has;
minor, the space in "F s" and "0 s" can be dropped too;
the and all the trailing 0... doesn't logically follow the one most significant digit.

So yes, although I find the original Microsoft documentation telling enough, it doesn't have to be necessarily my proposal, but it should be changed nevertheless to make it clearer.
Otherwise LGTM, thanks.

